2.20. Specific to Family cards
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If one or more Family cards have been issued for a card account, each
Family cardholder shall be entitled to use his/her MasterCard to conduct
transactions using the card account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
As the account holder, you are liable as guarantor with primary
liability for all use of the card account and the associated
costs, irrespective of whether the payments, withdrawals were
made using your own card or a Family card. The holder of a Family
card is also severally liable for his/her use of the card.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If you no longer wish the holder of a Family card to be entitled
to use your card account, you must inform &BANKNAVN. of this
without delay. &BANKNAVN. will subsequently block the card in
question. You must then cut the card into pieces and return it to
BEC Banken. The guarantee can only be terminated with effect from
the time at which the Family card for which the guarantee was
posted is returned and the account owing in &BANKNAVN.'s favour
has been cleared. The power of attorney will be terminated when
&BANKNAVN. receives notification of the death of the card account holder.
.sp 3mm
No supplementary services, including insurance policies, are linked to a
Family card.
